fix: Circuit breaker tripping causing chat network errors

Root cause: Circuit breaker opens after 3 embedding failures, causing all subsequent chat requests to fail immediately with CircuitBreakerError.

Fixes applied:
1. Increased circuit breaker tolerance (3→5 failures, 60s→120s timeout)
2. Better error handling in embedding service (empty input handling, detailed logging)
3. Graceful degradation when circuit breaker is open (user-friendly error messages)
4. Removed RAG context retrieval for product queries (was causing unnecessary failures)
5. Added health check endpoints for debugging:
   - GET /health/embedding - Test embedding model
   - GET /health/llm - Check LLM configuration
   - GET /health/circuit-breakers - Check circuit breaker states

Expected improvements:
- Error rate: 50% → <5%
- Circuit breaker trips: Rare (increased tolerance)
- User experience: Graceful degradation instead of "Network error"
- Debugging: Health endpoints for production monitoring

Zero cost impact - all code improvements only.